gw.plugin.reinsurance

Interface IReinsuranceConfigPlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public interface IReinsuranceConfigPlugin
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin
    Interface to a configurable module for configuring how out-of-the-box reinsurance should be behave.

      • getInclusionType

        RIAttachmentInclusionType getInclusionType(RIRisk ririsk,
                                           RIAgreement agreement)
        Return the default inclusion type for the given agreement and RI risk. Note that the system only stores the inclusion type of a (RIRisk, RIAgreement) pair if it is different from this default value. As the result, if this default value is changed, it will affect all the policy periods which use the default value including the bound ones, which in turn, requires ceding to be recalculated on those periods.
        Parameters:
        ririsk - the RI risk
        agreement - the agreement
        Returns:
        the inclusion type

      • getOverrideCededAmountForSurplusRITreaty

        MonetaryAmount getOverrideCededAmountForSurplusRITreaty(RIRisk ririsk,
                                                        SurplusRITreaty surplusTreaty)
        Used to set the ceded amount for a Surplus treaty to something less than the max allowed by lines times the gross retention. If the returned value is not null, the ceded amount will be overriden. If the return value is greater than the max allowed amount, the max allowed amount will be used.
        Parameters:
        ririsk - the RI risk
        surplusTreaty - the surplus treaty
        Returns:
        the override ceded amount

      • programCanCoverReinsurable

        boolean programCanCoverReinsurable(RIProgram program,
                                   Reinsurable reinsurable)
        Filter function which is used to restrict programs based on reinsurable. The program will already have been restricted to the correct RICoverageGroupType; this function allows for additional criteria (e.g. programs covering only particular regions or other risk characteristics).
        Parameters:
        program - The program in question
        reinsurable - The reinsurable to which program may be applied
        Returns:
        True if this program can be used to cover the given reinsurable, false otherwise

      • chooseReinsuranceProgram

        RIProgram chooseReinsuranceProgram(RIProgram[] candidates,
                                   Reinsurable reinsurable,
                                   java.util.Date effectiveDate,
                                   SearchType searchType)
        Filter function that takes a list of reinsurance programs which may be applicable to the given coverageGroup on the desired effective date. This function is called to choose the correct program from among the candidates. All programs in the list will already have passed the "programCanCoverReinsurable" test above.

        The system will attempt to make a sub-optimal program assignment if necessary, by considering draft programs and/or prior year programs. This method may therefore be called up to three times for a search; the stage of the search is indicated using the searchType parameter.

        Parameters:
        candidates - An array of RIProgram entities which apply to coverageGroup
        reinsurable - The reinsurable for which reinsurance is needed
        effectiveDate - The start date for which reinsurance is needed
        searchType - The type of programs in the candidate list (Active, Draft, or Prior Year)
        Returns:
        The RIProgram to attach to the reinsurable on this date, or null if there is nothing suitable.
